(1-x^2) > 0 \Leftrightarrow x \in [-1,1]
\int_{-1}^1 e^{-x^2} (1-x^2) dx = 2 \int_0^1 e^{-x^2} (1-x^2) dx = \frac 1 e + \frac {\sqrt \pi} 2{\rm erf}(1) 
